{"id":1235090043,"question_id":13,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 month, 2 weeks","timestamp":1713375896,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"4 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1235090043/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"44.8 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        // Create a map to store the values of Roman numerals\n        Map<Character, Integer> romanValues = new HashMap<>();\n        romanValues.put('I', 1);\n        romanValues.put('V', 5);\n        romanValues.put('X', 10);\n        romanValues.put('L', 50);\n        romanValues.put('C', 100);\n        romanValues.put('D', 500);\n        romanValues.put('M', 1000);\n        \n        int result = 0;\n        int prevValue = 0; // Initialize the previous value\n        \n        // Traverse the Roman numeral string from right to left\n        for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {\n            char currentChar = s.charAt(i);\n            int currentValue = romanValues.get(currentChar);\n            \n            // If the current value is less than the previous value, subtract it\n            if (currentValue < prevValue) {\n                result -= currentValue;\n            } else {\n                result += currentValue;\n            }\n            \n            // Update the previous value for the next iteration\n            prevValue = currentValue;\n        }\n        \n        return result;\n    }\n}\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
